@PatrikStas 
1: There are multiple ledgers, Domain Ledger (with txns like NYM, SCHEMA, ATTRIB, etc.), which is the main one for users data. and Pool Ledger, where information about the Nodes is stored (NODE txn). So, there are two genesis txn files (one for Domain ledger containing initial/gensis NYM txns, that is initial Trustees in the system, and one for the Pool ledger containing initial Nodes in the pool, that is NODE txns)
3: Indy Node service has 2 network interfaces: for node-to-node communication (consensus protocol), defined by node_ip and node_port, and for client-to-node communication (defined by client_ip, client_port), which receives requests and transactions from clients

